      "type": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "What is the key difference between teacher forcing and student forcing?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "Teacher forcing conditions on gold previous tokens during training, while student forcing conditions on the model's own generated tokens.",
        "Teacher forcing samples randomly, while student forcing always chooses the gold token.",
        "Teacher forcing is used only for evaluation, while student forcing is used only for data collection.",
        "Teacher forcing removes the softmax layer, while student forcing adds it back."
      ],
      "answer_index": 0,
      "explanation": "Teacher forcing supplies the correct previous tokens, making next-token learning easier. At generation time, the model no longer has those gold tokens and must condition on its own earlier outputs.",
